						               													<description>(Translated from the box and homepage)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A Christian strategy game with witnessing obligation as its focus!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In Oppdrag: Misjon the participants will build missionary bases, upgrade them to congregations and churches around the world.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To be able to build one, one has to have access to resources. As the term strategy hints at, you need to be smart and make a strategic plan deciding where it's favorable to build missionaries, in order to secure the resources you need. One may suddenly be struck by drought catastrophes or a grasshopper invasion, so nothing is predictable.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The aim is to collect 5000 missionary points, but in addition answer questions from 3 of the information cards you have received during the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;33 of the missionary organizations in Norway have written some information about their work and the countries where they evangelize in.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This game is clearly influenced by &amp;quot;The Settlers of Catan&amp;quot;. The basic gameplay with rolling for reaources and using these to build various things is lifted straight off of Settlers.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
